Ronnie
I drive my 63/23 almost daily. I put approximately 35,000 mi a year on it
(118,000 in 3 plus years). I commute from Tacoma, Washington to Bellevue (45
mi door to door) in addition to job sites, shows, campouts, vacations and
the what not (Washington, Oregon, California and Canada). I do nothing
special to it, just do the basic maintenance and drive. I am currently
replacing the 1600 sp motor, trans and reduction boxes (actually Ken at the
Bus Co. is). The Motor has just over 216,000 miles on it. the Tranny just
over 100,000 and the reduction boxes ???
The Person I bought the bus from put the first 98,000 mi on it in just over
a 9 year period.
why it held together so well is a mystery. just 6 months ago I checked the
compression and all 4 cylinders were between 112 and 117. Heck If the motor
wasn't leaking so much oil I would still be driving on it.


Shawn
Tacoma, WA
54, 61, & 63 Type II's


